        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-04-16 06:51:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThanks Maopeng.\nYes, fixed_ip_address is a list. Got the 1st string of the list as ip_address should work.\nHowever, it may be a common case that multiple ip addresses are defined in tosca (ipv4, ipv6...). The handling of ip address in vnflcm which always gets the 1st string is somehow a potential concern.\n\n1. Checked multivim, it seems that it does not strictly accept ip as string only.\n2. Checked openstack neutron api, it accepts multiple fixed_ip but the ip_address defined inside is normally a string.\n3. Checked with Lianhao before doing this patch, that all ip addresses should be sent to openstack finally.\n\nSo the question maybe where should we handle the ip_address if the list has several address items? In lcm or in multivim? For me, perhaps it should be better if addressed in multivim.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
